Key Match Events: David Wiese scored 13 runs and restricted Oman to 10 in the super over after the match was tied at the end of each side’s 20 overs.
Ruben Trumpelmann took four wickets, contributing to Oman's all-out score of 109 off 19.4 overs.
Mehran Khan took three wickets for seven runs off three overs, including two crucial wickets in the final over.
David Wiese hit a four and a six off the first two balls of the super over, setting a daunting target for Oman.
David Wiese took the wicket of Naseem Khushi in the super over, securing Namibia's victory.
Post-Match Reflections: David Wiese expressed that it was an emotionally draining evening and he was confident of steering Namibia to victory with both bat and ball in the super over.
Oman captain Aqib Ilyas defended the decision to opt for Bilal Khan as the super over bowler, despite the outcome.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a low-scoring thriller decided by a super over after both teams finished with 109 runs from their allotted 20 overs.
The pitch was difficult and did not play as expected, according to David Wiese.
